                "type": "text",
                "text": "You\u2019re doing exactly what I\u2019m trying to start in my apartment! During my undergrad I had a lot of fun making cheap quantum computing demos for people to learn from. A lot of what made this possible was 3d printing because I could make a box that held all the wires, circuit boards, and metal the exact way I needed. I didn\u2019t have to buy a whole custom assembly of parts or anything which made it feel way more accessible. So I just bought my own printer and I hope to get a soldering kit for my own at-home experiments!"
